snippet.textDisplay: So I hope I don’t get accused of trolling here as this is meant to be a constructive comment and I understand a lot is done that no one sees. However, with the uk in as much crisis as it is right now, with families relying on food banks to survive, i would love to see some youtubers do a £100 food bank challenge, or volunteer at one. I understand a lot of charitable work goes on that we don’t see as they don’t want hate for it or accused of only doing it for publicity, but I really feel that people in such privileged situations need to highlight what’s going on. I would have much more enjoyed a £50 video giving to someone else rather than using the money for more stuff for two very fortunate people.
